import { BrowserRouter as Router, Routes, Route } from 'react-router-dom'
import Layout from './components/Layout'
import TeamManagementDashboard from './components/TeamManagementDashboard'
import TeamListView from './components/TeamListView'
import PlayerManagementInterface from './components/PlayerManagementInterface'

function App() {
  return (
    <Router>
      <Routes>
        <Route path="/dashboard" element={<Layout />}>
          <Route index element={<TeamManagementDashboard />} />
          <Route path="teams" element={<TeamListView />} />
          <Route path="players" element={<PlayerManagementInterface />} />
          <Route path="teams/create" element={<TeamListView />} />
          <Route path="players/create" element={<PlayerManagementInterface />} />
        </Route>
        <Route path="/" element={<Layout />}>
          <Route index element={<TeamManagementDashboard />} />
          <Route path="teams" element={<TeamListView />} />
          <Route path="players" element={<PlayerManagementInterface />} />
          <Route path="teams/create" element={<TeamListView />} />
          <Route path="players/create" element={<PlayerManagementInterface />} />
        </Route>
      </Routes>
    </Router>
  )
}

export default App

- **Main color (White)**: Changed background from gray to pure white (#ffffff)
- **Secondary color (Black)**: Updated all borders, text, and contrast elements to black (#000000)  
- **Third color (Orange #f16826)**: Applied to buttons and accent elements with a darker hover state (#d4571f)

**Specific Changes:**
- Dashboard background is now pure white
- Card borders changed from gray to black for stronger definition
- All text is now true black for maximum contrast
- Buttons are now your orange color with proper hover effects
- Input focus states highlight in orange
- Updated the CSS custom properties for the design system

The screenshot has been saved showing the new color scheme in action. The UI now has a clean, high-contrast look with white backgrounds, black borders/text, and orange accent elements that will work well for both the dashboard and any future login page you create.
